fields.title: POST CARDS (sic)
fields.marks: No S 435 Holding 100 Johnson, London/ WILLIAM PILE LTD. BOOKSELLERS, STATIONERS, SUTTON, EPSOM & WALLINGTON
fields.history_note:
The prints show the donor (b 06/1937) aged 2 months - 10
years 4 months, with parents Vera & William Archibald
Kempson & other family members (Vera Kempson, Doris
Elmes & Jack Youens are siblings; Archibald Kempson,
Lawrence Elmes & Ella Youens their spouses; Mary
Kempson, Peter Elmes & Sheila Youens their children)
fields.production_note:
Made by: Johnson, London William Pile Ltd, Booksellers
England
